# Programming Standards — `actions`

Use this rule as a lightweight gate. The detailed operating standard lives in:
[.cursor/skills/senior-coding-actions/SKILL.md](mdc:.cursor/skills/senior-coding-actions/SKILL.md)

This is the umbrella rule. Specialized companion rules cover:
- web3 transaction and ABI safety,
- UI/brand consistency,
- branch-aware changelog/version policy.

## How to apply

1. For any code-change task, read and follow the `senior-coding-actions` skill before editing files.
2. Treat the skill as the single source of truth; do not duplicate or invent a parallel standard.
3. If this rule and the skill ever diverge, update the rule to match the skill.

## Hard stops

Stop and ask the user before proceeding if any of these would be violated:
- ABI is being authored inline in TypeScript instead of JSON.
- A write transaction skips `estimateGas` preflight without a documented wallet limitation.
- Lint, type-check, or build is red at handoff.
- New project content (comments/docs/changelog/UI copy) is written in a language other than English.
